# Git commit and push workflow

Whenever you create a **`git commit`** in this workspace (fixes, features, chores), **`git push`** the **current branch** to **`origin`** in the same workflow before reporting task completion — unless push fails (network/auth) or the user explicitly asked not to push.

Combine when possible: commit then push immediately; do not stop at "committed locally only."

The repository may also configure `core.hooksPath` to `.githooks` so that `git commit` triggers a **`post-commit`** hook that runs `git push`; do not rely on hooks alone — if you bypass hooks or hooks fail, run **`git push`** yourself.
